funds set to take on mercer‚Äôs new longevity solution product lifetimeplus early next quarter the company said its investment option was the world‚Äôs first pooled mortality investment fund designed to protect more australians against the risk of outliving their savings mercer managing director and pacific market leader david anderson said retirement would be a financial challenge for many ‚Äúlife might be simple but comfortable for the first decade or so but once savings run out the age pension will only provide about half the amount required for a ‚Äòcomfortable lifestyle‚Äô according to asfa association of superannuation funds of australia‚Äù anderson said vicsuper chief executive michael dundon said he was impressed to witness such an innovative product development happening in the retirement income space ‚Äúto ensure our members can maintain their desired lifestyles in retirement we believe we must provide appropriate solutions which manage the risks they face as well as providing for their income needs‚Äù dundon said ‚Äúan adviserled incomelayering approach to building a member‚Äôs retirement portfolio can provide the best outcome for our members ‚Äúusing an innovative product suite is fundamental to this approach‚Äù lifetimeplus is expected to be primarily delivered to consumers via financial advisers since circumstances upon entering the longevity investment including a member‚Äôs age and superannuation account balance will directly determine the product‚Äôs suitability effectiveness and productivity of their returns mercer senior partner and senior actuary david knox said the investor must have a retirement pension in order to enter the shared pooled investment knox explained that what differentiated the option from others was that it was deliberately biased towards those who lived longest in order to give those members the sustained confidence that they would have enough savings to maintain their lifestyle until they died apart from assessing the suitability of the product for each investor on a casebycase basis advisers will also be responsible for delivering imperative product information to members anderson said despite lifetimeplus initially only being delivered by financial planners it could be expected to evolve over time become a retail fund and eventually have the potential to be made directly available to consumers ¬´ back to articles industry highlights hub recruits btfg exec afa announces new ceo as fox steps down perpetual hires longtime count boss senate ticks raise sector stability hopes nab slashes junior advice roles anz backs down from wealth in australia        next video regulatory roundtable ep  the first episode our industry guests discussionview more video the evolution of aged care rachel lane gives an overview of developmentsview more   next most read articles asic assetbased fees stance disappointing established platforms lag newcomers feature estate planning internal review leads to k fee cuts managers advisers recognise etf benefits savings outside super to accelerate featured articles aiofp amends constitution for tpb recognition feature navigating the costs of a long life deeper integration for roboadvice on the way change still all the rage through  supreme court denies timbercorp investors small licensee pi investigation under way    next contact level   hunter street sydney nsw  content newsinsightopinionappointmentsfinancial planninginvestmentsuperannuationaccountinginsurancetechnology information aboutadvertisesubscribecontact usprivacy policyevents social linkedintwitter website design¬†by redcloud digital products archive  mercer capital ‚åÇ obtain a proposal careers login contact us üîésearch for mercer capital products creating strategic value through financial technology newest book now available creating strategic value through financial technology illustrates the potential benefits of fintech to banks both large and small so that they can gain a better understanding of finte