 navigation search mercer llc type subsidiary llc industry professional services founded  ¬†years ago¬† headquarters new york city new york us number of locations  cities in  countries key people julio portalatin chairman and ceo products human resource consulting services including retirement health  benefits human capital surveys  products communication investments outsourcing and mergers  acquisitions revenue  billioncitation needed number of employees   parent marsh  mclennan companies website wwwmercercom mercer is the worlds largest human resources consulting firm headquartered in new york city mercer has more than  employees is based in more than  countries and operates internationally in more than  countries mercer is a subsidiary of global professional services firm marsh  mclennan contents  history  regions  see also  references  external links historyedit started in the united states in  as the employee benefits department of marsh  mclennan inc the company took the name of ‚Äúwilliam m mercer‚Äù in  when marsh  mclennan acquired william m mercer limited a canadian firm founded by william manson mercer in vancouver in  in  mercer became a wholly owned subsidiary of marsh  mclennan companies inc in  its name was changed to mercer human resource consulting in  the company acquired houston txbased synhrgy hr technologies a human resources technology and outsourcing services company also in  mercer admitted giving the nyse board a compensation report that contained omissions and inaccuracies that led to a  million pay package for former nyse chairman richard grasso mercer had been brought in to advise the stock exchange on grassos  contract and his request for  million the consultancy returned  in fees it collected from the nyse and provided key documents in the lawsuit in  the company became simply mercer also in  mercer acquired h√∂fer vorsorgemanagement a german actuarial and retirement consulting firm at the time the acquisition reportedly gave mercer the top market position in germany in  mercers italian human capital consulting business merged with tesi an italian competitor the combined business mercer tesi was noted at the time to be the largest hr consultancy in italy in  mercer acquired orc worldwide an expert in international work assignments also in  mercer acquired brecksville ohiobased innovative process administration llc ipa a health benefits and technology provider in  mercer acquired fort lauderdale flbased mahoney  associates a defined contribution plan provider also in  mercer acquired alicia smith  associates a washington dcbased medicaid policy consulting firm in  mercer acquired british columbiabased hall consulting limited hcl an hr consultant and salary surveyor focusing on the mining and energy business also in  mercer acquired pricewaterhousecoopers pension windup termination administration business in canada also in  mercer acquired global remuneration solutions grs a south african compensation and benefits survey data and rewards information provider in  mercer acquired norwell mabased transition assist a private health care exchange specializing in coverage for medicareeligible retirees also in  mercer acquired jeitosa group international a business and technology consultancy and acquired a  stake in south africabased employee benefits specialist alexander forbes later that year mercer acquired swiss private markets manager and consultant scm and denarius a santiago chilebased consulting firm focused on compensation and benefits survey and information products in  mercer made two acquisitions it acquired hopkinton mabased comptryx a workforce metrics company offering surveying modeling and analytics services and also acquired hrbs a provider of career and talent consulting and information services to clients across asia with concentrated strength in hong kong singapore and mainland china regionsedit since january  mercer has been organized into three geographic regions each with a regional president north america europac europe  pacific markets of australia and new zealand and growth markets asia africa and latin america headquarters for the north american region are in new york city for europac in london and for growth markets in singapore less than half of the organization‚Äôs employees are based in north america see alsoedit list of most expensive cities for expatriate employees referencesedit  a b about us mercercom retrieved ¬†  a b acquisition by mercer to give new energy to highflying synhrgy houston business journals  retrieved ¬†  acing the mercer interview ‚Äì an overview of the firm managementconsultedcom  retrieved ¬†  william mercer changes name indiatimescom  retrieved ¬†  hr figures prominently in stock exchange scandal hrblrcom  archived from the original on july   retrieved ¬†  mercer hr consulting rebrands as mercer professionalpensionscom  retrieved ¬†  mercer acquires h√∂fer vorsorgemanagement in germany newstopconsultantcom  retrieved ¬†  mercer  tesi deal creates italian market leader growthbusinesscouk  retrieved ¬†  mercer acquires orc worldwide to strengthen its capabilities in global workforce management hrmagazinecouk  retrieved ¬†  mercer buys mahoney  associates practices southfloridabusinessjournalcom  retrieved ¬†  mercer acquires alicia smith  associates in dc washington business journal  retrieved ¬†  mercer acquires hall consulting growthbusinesscouk  retrieved ¬†  mercer to buy pwcs canadian pension windup business businessinsurancecom  retrieved ¬†  mercer in deal for global remuneration solutions mindbenchcom  retrieved ¬†  mercer expands health care exchange offerings with acquisition businessinsurancecom  retrieved ¬†  mercer acquires jeitosa group international workforcecom  retrieved ¬†  mercer to buy alexander forbes stake bdlivecoza  retrieved ¬†  mercer acquires swiss private markets managerconsultant pensions  investments online  retrieved ¬†  marsh  mclennan unit mercer buys denarius rttnewscom  retrieved 